Bosten Lake, a large freshwater lake located in northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, has turned into a frozen winter playground during Spring Festival. Temperatures dropped to minus 20 degrees Celsius in Bohu County where the lake is located. Check out this video of tourists enjoying activities on snow and ice. (Cover image via VCG, video provided by Nian Lei) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)